						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Venkaṭēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1322 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1244, (Duṁdubhi) Mārgaśira, ba. 15, Solar eclipse, corresponding to 1322 A.D. December 9, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>Registers the setting up of six pillars <hi rend="italic">(āru kaṁbhamulu)</hi> in the temple Ishṭa Kāmīśvaradēva by Appana-Peggaḍa Annaṁgāru and also gift of land measuring one <hi rend="italic">pandumu</hi> as his son's <hi rend="italic">vṛitti</hi> to the temple by him.</p>						

						</summary>
